  {
    "_id": "hxbSpecter000001",
    "name": "Hexbound Specter",
    "type": "feat",
    "img": "icons/magic/death/undead-ghost-scream-teal.webp",
    "system": {
      "description": {
        "value": "<h2>Level 6: Hexbound Specter</h2>\n<p>Once per Long Rest, when a hostile creature is reduced to 0 Hit Points inside your Hex Aura, you can bind a fragment of its departing spirit. The spirit appears as a Hexbound Specter in an unoccupied space you can see inside your Hex Aura.</p>\n<p>The Hexbound Specter is friendly to you and your allies. It shares your initiative count and acts immediately after your turn.</p>\n<p>The Hexbound Specter obeys your verbal commands to the best of its ability. You can issue or change a command verbally on your turn, requiring no action. The command can be specific, such as “attack that creature,” or general, such as “defend me,” “guard this passage,” or “stay beside that ally.”</p>\n<p>Once the command is completed, or if the specter has no command it can follow, it takes the Dodge action and attempts to return to you if it can see you, or to the last place it knew you were.</p>\n<p>The Hexbound Specter remains until it drops to 0 Hit Points, until you dismiss it, until you summon another Hexbound Specter, or until you finish a Long Rest.</p>\n<p>The Hexbound Specter cannot create other undead, cannot reduce a creature’s Hit Point maximum, and cannot regain Hit Points except as described in Hexbound Specter Healing.</p>\n<h3>Hexbound Specter Stat Block</h3>\n<p>Medium Undead, Neutral</p>\n<p><strong>Armor Class:</strong> 12 + half your Proficiency Bonus, rounded down</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Points:</strong> 10 + five times your Warlock level</p>\n<p><strong>Speed:</strong> 0 ft., fly 50 ft. (hover)</p>\n<p><strong>Damage Resistances:</strong> Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, Thunder; Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing</p>\n<p><strong>Damage Immunities:</strong> Necrotic, Poison</p>\n<p><strong>Condition Immunities:</strong> Charmed, Exhaustion, Frightened, Grappled, Paralyzed, Petrified, Poisoned, Prone, Restrained, Unconscious</p>\n<p><strong>Senses:</strong> Darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 10 + your Proficiency Bonus</p>\n<p><strong>Languages:</strong> Understands the languages it knew in life and the languages you know, but cannot speak</p>\n<h3>Traits</h3>\n<p><strong>Incorporeal Movement.</strong> The specter can move through creatures and objects as if they were Difficult Terrain. It takes 1d10 Force damage if it ends its turn inside an object.</p>\n<p><strong>Sunlight Sensitivity.</strong> While in sunlight and outside your Hex Aura, the specter has Disadvantage on attack rolls and Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on sight.</p>\n<h3>Actions</h3>\n<p><strong>Life Drain.</strong> Melee Spell Attack: +4 plus your Charisma modifier to hit, reach 5 feet, one creature. Hit: 3d6 Necrotic damage.</p>\n<p>The damage increases to 4d6 when you reach Warlock level 10 and 5d6 when you reach Warlock level 14.</p>\n<p><strong>Foundry actor:</strong> A <em>Hexbound Specter</em> NPC actor is included in the <strong>Hexblade Warlock: Actors</strong> compendium. The included actor is a baseline importable creature for the DM. Adjust its AC, HP, and Life Drain damage according to the summoning Warlock’s level and Charisma modifier.</p>",
        "chat": ""
      },
      "source": {
        "custom": "Hexblade Patron Playtest",
        "rules": "2024",
        "revision": 1,
        "license": "Homebrew Playtest",
        "book": ""
